		(uuid "fff0d1e4-0e31-4a91-8576-24381d4266b2")
	)
	(text "LM317A:\nΔV_{OUT}=~3V (at ≥ 10ma)\nUse 120Ω load resistor\n\nT8/T20Q144 VCORE Requirements\nTypical: 1.15V ~ 1.25V, Absolute max: 1.42V\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 146.05 154.94 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left bottom)
		)
		(uuid "36373244-3f47-47b9-8cf8-e846bf57bdef")
	)
	(text "TPS5430 design with MLCC per:\nhttps://www.ti.com/lit/an/slva237c/slva237c.pdf"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 170.18 19.05 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "38789033-e852-485a-8f7b-8761d61db34d")
	)
	(text "18.3 VAC C.T. arrives on pins 1/5. Rectified DC\nleaves on pin 4, is externally smoothed by a\n17-23mF capacitor and returns on pin 2.\n\nDespite being labeled 9V_UNREG in the CBM\nschematics, the actual voltage is closer to 12V.\n\nPins 8/9 are not used by the replacement board.\nThe PET power supply delivers 17 VAC on pins 8/9,\nwhich was used by the original mainboard to\nproduce +16V DC for internal accessories.\n\nThe CRT gets power directly from the transformer.\n\nCapactiors must be derated min ~30% for AC:\n12V AC * 1.415 = ~17V DC\n\nUse min 25V for caps connected to +9V_UNREG.\nNote that MLCCs must also be significantly\nderated for DC bias."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 29.21 130.81 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left bottom)
		)
		(uuid "39bedb57-e128-4b36-b3c2-6c3350b94506")
	)
	(text "Power Indicator"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 17.78 144.78 0)
		(effects
			(font
